			<!--<p>EHRI-DR-19430309-IT_EN</p>
      <p/>
      <p>Report of the envoy in Rome, Massimo Magistrati, of 9 March 1943 for the Ministry of
        Foreign Affairs in Rome</p>
      <p/>
      <p>Incoming telegram, by courier, no. 1556 R.</p>
      <p>Deciphered by: F.M. Cleartext</p>
      <p/>
      <p>Sender: R. Legation Sofia</p>
      <p>Sofia, 9.3.43 (XXI)</p>
      <p>Rome, 12/idem</p>
      <p/>
      <p>[One 1-line stamp reading: “13 Mar. 1943 Year XXI]</p>
      <p/>
      <p>Assigned: A.G.</p>
      <p><space> </space>A.E.M.</p>
      <p/>
      <p>0135 – My telegram by courier no. 0121 of the 5th inst.</p>-->
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19430309-IT_01.jpg"/>
			<p>What has been reported in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1026" type="subject">neutral countries</term>, namely that the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295">Bulgarian Government</orgName> is said to be negotiating at the
				same time with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">Germany</term> and with <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">Great Britain</placeName>
				concerning the removal from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName> of
				significant groups of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Israelites,</term> is true.</p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">Germany</term> has offered to transfer the Bulgarian
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish groups</term> to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghettoes</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> and has asked the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295">Bulgarian government</orgName> to pay the sum of five-hundred
				marks per person for transport costs and in exchange for property seized locally. <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_bulgarians"
					>Bulgarians</term> have resisted this request <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-DR-19430309-IT_02.jpg"/> and for the time being nothing has
				been decided as yet on the financial question. However, the departures of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> for <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> have already begun, albeit limited to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish groups</term> living in the new <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgarian</placeName> territories, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/738770/thrace.html">Thrace</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/735355/makedonia.html">Macedonia</placeName>, where there are <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish communities</term> that have been estimated at
				approx. twenty-thousand individuals. As for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject"
					>Jews</term> in the ancient <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgarian</placeName>
				territory nothing definite has been decided, because reportedly the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295">Bulgarian government</orgName> is opposing a marked <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-212" type="subject">resistance</term>.</p>
			<p>With <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">Great
					Britain</placeName> there have been negotiations through the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-1373">Swiss Government</orgName> about dispatching to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6254930/palestine.html">Palestine</placeName> four-thousand adult <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_bulgarians">Bulgarian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> and four-thousand <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term> children. But the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">Reich</term> has stepped in and in a certain sense
				has “vetoed” this departure, judging, as usual, that it is dangerous to transfer to an enemy territory <pb n="3"
					facs="EHRI-DR-19430309-IT_03"/> such decidedly anti-German elements. In the end, apparently, the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295">Bulgarian Government</orgName> has resumed these negotiations
				despite that “veto”, limiting them to the four-thousand children who would be accompanied by no more than five-hundred adults. This
				negotiation as well, however, seems to encounter problems of a financial nature.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_dr_magistrati_massimo">Magistrati</persName></p>
